---
import SAGPLayout from "../../../../layouts/SAGPLayout.astro";
---

<SAGPLayout title="Past Conferences & Archives | SAGP">

<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="kicker">Conference Archive</div>
    <h1>Decades of scholarly conversation.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      Since 1953, SAGP conferences and newsletters have preserved a record of
      research, dialogue, and community in Ancient Greek philosophy.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>About SAGP conferences</h2>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p>
      Traditionally, SAGP has organized sessions with two or more speakers at
      the regional meetings of the American Philosophical Association and at the
      annual meeting of the Society for Classical Studies.
    </p>

    <p>
      In accordance with the regulations of those associations, speakers are
      chosen by blind review of submitted papers. Evaluators are drawn from the
      SAGP Board of Directors.
    </p>

    <p>
      SAGP also holds an annual conference, usually in the autumn. The conference
      has traditionally taken place at a university, with its location rotating
      among constituencies, while online formats have increasingly made
      participation possible for scholars across the world.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>Recent conferences</h2>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Annual Conference 2025</h3>
      <p>
        Plato, Aristotle, Presocratic ontology, and Stoic epistemology.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="/events/annual-conference/2025/">View the 2025 program</a>
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Annual Conference 2024</h3>
      <p>
        Pre-Socratics, Socrates and Plato, Aristotle, and Post-Aristotelian
        philosophy.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="/events/annual-conference/2024/">View the 2024 program</a>
      </p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Historical archive</h3>
      <p>
        SAGP newsletters and conference materials preserve a record of scholarly
        activity extending back to the Society’s early decades.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="#">Archive link to be restored</a>
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>Institutional memory</h2>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p>
      The conference archive is more than a record of past programs. It is a
      record of the Society’s continuing scholarly life: the questions scholars
      asked, the texts they returned to, and the conversations they sustained
      across generations.
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      Future enhancement: restore the original digital archive link and decide
      whether newsletters, programs, and accepted papers should be presented as
      a searchable archive.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</SAGPLayout>
